Known cut features:
Dealing with locations
Affects like stone, darkness, poison, etc...


User table metadata: create table user ( ID int NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, email VARCHAR(100), salt VARCHAR(12), password VARCHAR(32), created DATETIME, PRIMARY KEY (ID) )

Location
name(varchar(50)) x(int) y(int) width(int) height(int)

explanation:
Should check the map for proper locations

Item 
id(int) location(varchar(50)) name(varchar(50)) sell(int) cost(int) use(bool) all(bool) temporary(bool) requiredLevel(int) changeStatus(varchar(10))
		hitPoints, maxHitPoints, magicPoints, maxMagicPoints, strength, agility, intelligence, stamina, luck, attack, defense, accuracy, evasion (int)
		//imageLocation(varchar(255)) //loads from local hosted file

explanation:
location -> id from the table Locations

use true  -> usable item => dont look for attributes
use false -> equiptment  => dont look for affect

all true -> affects whole party
else ...

temporary true -> this attribute addition will be removed after battle

changeStatus { normal, darkness, poison, stone, KO }


Spell
id(int) location(varchar(50)) name(varchar(50)) sell(int) cost(int) white(bool) requiredLevel(int) type(varchar(10)) all(bool) applyOn(bool) changeStatus(varchar(10))
		hitPoints, strength, agility, intelligence, stamina, luck, attack, defense, accuracy, evasion (int)
		//hp(int) -> For example hp(30) means give 30 hp to charecter, but hp(-100) means make 100 dmg do character. If the spell dosn't do anything with
		//the hp of the character then it should be hp(0) coz in the game logic I will sum every property with the character properties.
		
		1, 'Cornelia', 'Cure', 50, 100, TRUE, 1, 'neutral', FALSE, TRUE, 'normal', 30, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0 ,0
		2, 'Cornelia', 'Harm', 50, 100, TRUE, 1, 'holy', FALSE, FALSE, 'normal', -50, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0 ,0
		
		

level { 1, 2, ... 8 }

applyOn 0 -> enemy
applyOn 1 -> self


type { neutral, earth, fire, water, wind, holy, dark }

if(white) -> white magic
else	  -> black magic


   if all -> apply to all units
   else -> apply to selected unit

Connection Tables
	User Item
	userId(int) itemId(int) quantity(int)
	
	User Spell
	userId(int) spellId(int)
	
	Creature Spells
	creatureId(int) spellId(int)
	
Creature
id(int) location(varchar(50)) name(varchar(50)) type(varchar(10)) experienceEarn(int)
hitPoints, maxHitPoints, magicPoints, maxMagicPoints, strength, agility, intelligence, stamina, luck, attack, defense, accuracy, evasion (int)
imageX(int), imageY(int) imageWidth(int), imageHeight(int)// load from big local sprite








